  'You are appraising the property at 3301 Reidville Road, Moore, SC 29369 (3BR/2BA, 1,840 SF, built 1998, brick ranch · Reidville Estates). Eminent domain/condemnation. SCDOT is acquiring a residential property for the Reidville Road corridor widening project. The property owner disputes SCDOT''s market condition analysis. You must establish market conditions as of the date of taking, addressing both general market conditions and the effect of the project announcement on the subject''s market area. Section 6 — Market Analysis — requires you to identify which market indicators and external factors are present in the data package, classify each present indicator as Improving, Stable, Declining, or Market-Dependent based on the indicator data and external context, and write a market-supported rationale citing specific data from the indicator table or external context. Indicators not evidenced in the data package must be left unchecked. Every classification must be grounded in specific evidence — this assignment evaluates evidence-based market analysis, not pattern recognition or reflexive checklist behavior.'
FROM scenario_categories WHERE code = 'M2-S6-C2';

