  '{"subject": {"address_summary": "5520 Augusta Street, Greenville, SC 29605", "subject_summary": "3BR/2BA, 1,740 SF, built 2001, ranch · Augusta Road Corridor", "school": "Greenville County - J.L. Mann HS zone", "effective_date": "April 15, 2022 (retrospective)", "context_label": "Litigation Context", "context_text": "Shareholder dispute involving a residential portfolio holding company. Value as of a specific buyout date is contested. The dispute centers on whether the market was at its peak or already in decline as of April 15, 2022. You must determine the precise state of market conditions on this exact date."}, "tables": [{"label": "", "cols": ["Indicator", "Prior Period (Oct 2021-Apr 2022)", "Current Period (Oct 2021-Apr 2022)"], "rows": [["Closed Sales", "44", "49"], ["Active Listings", "5", "4"], ["Median Days on Market", "10", "9"], ["Median Sale Price", "$231,500", "$249,800"], ["List-to-Sale Price Ratio", "103.9%", "106.2%"], ["Absorption Rate", "1.2 months", "1.0 months"], ["Mortgage Rate (effective date)", "~3.9%", "~5.0%"]]}], "external": "Mortgage rates crossed 5.0% for the first time in approximately 10 years in April 2022, widely reported in the financial press. However, rate locks already in place for pending transactions buffered near-term demand. As of April 15, 2022, demand indicators remained at or near peak levels. The rate increase had been announced but its full demand impact had not yet registered in closed sale data.", "factors": [{"id": "abs", "label": "Absorption rate trend"}, {"id": "dom", "label": "Days on market trend"}, {"id": "lts", "label": "List-to-sale price ratio trend"}, {"id": "msp", "label": "Median sale price trend"}, {"id": "inv", "label": "Active listing inventory level"}, {"id": "rate", "label": "Mortgage rate inflection (5.0% threshold crossing)"}, {"id": "post", "label": "May-December 2022 demand deterioration"}, {"id": "sea", "label": "Seasonal demand pattern"}], "net_conclusion": "Market was at or near peak as of April 15, 2022. Demand indicators confirm this in contemporaneous data. The mortgage rate inflection is a real, documented forward-looking risk factor appropriately noted in the narrative, but it had not yet registered in demand data as of this precise date.", "commentary": "Scenario 8 requires surgical precision about the state of the market on a specific date. The ability to describe what was knowable and reflected in data as of an exact date - no more, no less - is perhaps the most demanding retrospective skill. An appraiser who says the market was already declining as of April 15 cannot support that position with contemporaneous closed sale data and will be effectively cross-examined on it.", "classification_options": ["Improving", "Stable", "Declining", "Market-Dependent"], "min_rationale_chars": 20}'::jsonb,
  '{"factors": {"abs": {"present": true, "classification": "Improving", "rationale": "1.2 to 1.0 months as of April 15, 2022 - still accelerating as of this precise date. Contemporaneous closed sale data confirms peak conditions."}, "dom": {"present": true, "classification": "Stable", "rationale": "10 to 9 days - essentially unchanged as of the effective date. Demand velocity maintained at near-peak levels as of April 15."}, "lts": {"present": true, "classification": "Improving", "rationale": "103.9 to 106.2% - still accelerating over-ask premiums as of April 15, 2022. Peak market signal confirmed in contemporaneous data."}, "msp": {"present": true, "classification": "Improving", "rationale": "+7.9% - peak appreciation rate as of this date. Contemporaneous closed sales all reflect pre-effective-date market conditions."}, "inv": {"present": true, "classification": "Improving", "rationale": "5 to 4 actives - effectively zero supply as of April 15, 2022. Near-peak constrained supply conditions."}, "rate": {"present": true, "classification": "Market-Dependent", "rationale": "Rates crossed the 5.0% psychological threshold in April 2022 - a documented, verifiable forward-looking risk factor. However, as of April 15, closed sale data had not yet reflected the demand impact. Market-Dependent appropriately captures a real but not-yet-materialized risk."}, "post": {"present": false, "rationale": "CRITICAL DISTRACTOR: Rate increases did not affect closed sale data until May-June 2022 and beyond. Using subsequent deterioration data constitutes hindsight. As of April 15, 2022, no closed sale data reflects the demand impact of the rate increase."}, "sea": {"present": false, "rationale": "No seasonal data was provided. This is a distractor."}}}'::jsonb
