  '{"subject": {"address_summary": "7744 Old Buncombe Road, Greenville, SC 29617", "subject_summary": "3BR/1.5BA, 1,410 SF, built 1978, ranch (representative of portfolio) · North Greenville Corridor - Berea area", "school": "Greenville County - Berea area schools", "effective_date": "December 31, 2021 (retrospective)", "context_label": "Litigation Context", "context_text": "Bankruptcy trustee proceeding. The debtor''s expert values the portfolio using broad metro market data showing a strong improving market. The trustee''s expert argues the relevant submarket was already plateauing. You must define the correct market area, identify any submarket divergence, and form an independent, defensible conclusion using only contemporaneous data."}, "tables": [{"label": "", "cols": ["Indicator", "Broad Market (Jun-Dec 2021)", "Broad Market (Current)", "Submarket (Jun-Dec 2021)", "Submarket (Current)"], "rows": [["Closed Sales", "218", "241", "19", "16"], ["Active Listings", "31", "18", "4", "5"], ["Median DOM", "14", "10", "18", "22"], ["Median Sale Price", "$187,500", "$203,400", "$178,500", "$181,200"], ["List-to-Sale Ratio", "102.8%", "106.1%", "101.4%", "101.9%"], ["Absorption Rate", "1.8 months", "1.2 months", "2.3 months", "2.7 months"]]}], "external": "The broad Greenville County market was experiencing strong appreciation driven by migration demand and low rates as of December 31, 2021. The Old Buncombe/Berea corridor submarket contains older housing stock (1960s-1980s construction) with deferred maintenance concerns and proximity to industrial uses - factors that have historically suppressed demand growth relative to the broader metro. No major employment shock or demand driver was specific to this submarket as of the effective date.", "factors": [{"id": "b_abs", "label": "Broad market absorption rate trend"}, {"id": "b_msp", "label": "Broad market median price trend"}, {"id": "b_dom", "label": "Broad market DOM and list-to-sale trends"}, {"id": "s_abs", "label": "Submarket absorption rate trend"}, {"id": "s_dom", "label": "Submarket days on market trend"}, {"id": "s_msp", "label": "Submarket median price trend"}, {"id": "s_lts", "label": "Submarket list-to-sale ratio trend"}, {"id": "stock", "label": "Housing stock and use proximity factor"}, {"id": "post", "label": "Post-effective-date submarket data (2022)"}, {"id": "broad", "label": "Debtor''s broad market data as controlling analysis"}], "net_conclusion": "The appropriate market area is the submarket. While the broad Greenville County market was strongly improving as of December 31, 2021, the relevant submarket showed muted improvement - stable pricing with slightly softening demand indicators. The debtor''s expert applies an incorrect market area. Stable/Market-Dependent is the appropriate submarket classification.", "commentary": "Scenario 9 combines submarket divergence analysis with the retrospective hard-wall requirement. The debtor''s expert makes a common litigation error: using the most favorable available market data (the strong broad metro) while ignoring conditions in the actual competitive market area. Students must demonstrate the market area selection methodology and apply the submarket data that controls. The methodological distractor tests whether students can identify a market area error as distinct from a data error.", "classification_options": ["Improving", "Stable", "Declining", "Market-Dependent"], "min_rationale_chars": 20}'::jsonb,
  '{"factors": {"b_abs": {"present": true, "classification": "Improving", "rationale": "1.8 to 1.2 months - strong broad market improvement as of December 31, 2021. The debtor''s expert is directionally correct about broad market conditions."}, "b_msp": {"present": true, "classification": "Improving", "rationale": "+8.5% broad market appreciation - a genuine improving signal in the broader Greenville County market as of the effective date."}, "b_dom": {"present": true, "classification": "Improving", "rationale": "Broad market DOM and list-to-sale ratio both improving - confirming the debtor''s expert''s characterization of the broad market, which is however the wrong market area."}, "s_abs": {"present": true, "classification": "Market-Dependent", "rationale": "Rose from 2.3 to 2.7 months in the submarket - slight softening that diverges from the broad market improvement. Market-Dependent reflects this early, unresolved directional signal in the correct market area."}, "s_dom": {"present": true, "classification": "Declining", "rationale": "Rose from 18 to 22 days in the submarket - homes taking longer despite overall market strength. A meaningful divergence signal in the correct market area."}, "s_msp": {"present": true, "classification": "Stable", "rationale": "+1.5% in the submarket vs. +8.5% in the broad market - effective real price stagnation. Far below the broad market appreciation rate."}, "s_lts": {"present": true, "classification": "Stable", "rationale": "101.4 to 101.9% - modest and essentially flat in the submarket. Not reflecting the strong over-ask premiums seen in the broad market."}, "stock": {"present": true, "classification": "Declining", "rationale": "Older stock and industrial adjacency represent structural submarket weaknesses evidenced by the divergence from broad market trends. An external factor with a documented, suppressive effect on demand in this specific corridor."}, "post": {"present": false, "rationale": "CRITICAL DISTRACTOR: 2022 submarket data - even if showing improvement - is after the hard wall. The analysis must be limited to what was knowable and reflected in data as of December 31, 2021."}, "broad": {"present": false, "rationale": "METHODOLOGICAL DISTRACTOR: The broad market data is not wrong - it is the wrong market area. The controlling analysis uses data from the competitive supply area for the subject properties. Using broad market data for a submarket property overstates conditions and is a USPAP market area definition error."}}}'::jsonb
FROM scenarios s
JOIN scenario_categories sc ON sc.id = s.category_id
JOIN module_sections ms ON ms.id = sc.section_id
JOIN section_fields f ON f.section_id = ms.id AND f.field_key = 'market_indicator_analysis'
WHERE sc.code = 'M2-S6-C2'
  AND s.order_index = 9;

-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
-- Scenario 10: 118 Montague Avenue, Greenville — Probate Transitioning Market Dispute (Montague Heights)
-- Category M2-S6-C2 #10 · difficulty 'expert'
-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
INSERT INTO scenarios
  (category_id, order_index, difficulty, title, scenario_text)
SELECT id, 10,
  'expert',
  '118 Montague Avenue, Greenville — Probate Transitioning Market Dispute (Montague Heights)',
  'You are appraising the property at 118 Montague Avenue, Greenville, SC 29609 (4BR/2BA, 2,180 SF, built 1965, brick traditional · Montague Heights). Estate/probate dispute. Two heirs dispute the date-of-death value. Heir A''s appraiser relies on 12-month trailing appreciation to argue Strongly Improving. Heir B''s appraiser relies only on 6-month current data to argue Declining. You must analyze all available data as of August 12, 2022 only, resolve the competing conclusions, and write a complete, USPAP-compliant market condition narrative for the probate court. Section 6 — Market Analysis — requires you to identify which market indicators and external factors are present in the data package, classify each present indicator as Improving, Stable, Declining, or Market-Dependent based on the indicator data and external context, and write a market-supported rationale citing specific data from the indicator table or external context. Indicators not evidenced in the data package must be left unchecked. Every classification must be grounded in specific evidence — this assignment evaluates evidence-based market analysis, not pattern recognition or reflexive checklist behavior.'
FROM scenario_categories WHERE code = 'M2-S6-C2';

INSERT INTO model_answers
  (scenario_id, field_id, answer_text, field_options_override, model_data)
SELECT
  s.id,
  f.id,
  '',
  '{"subject": {"address_summary": "118 Montague Avenue, Greenville, SC 29609", "subject_summary": "4BR/2BA, 2,180 SF, built 1965, brick traditional · Montague Heights", "school": "Greenville County - Wade Hampton HS zone", "effective_date": "August 12, 2022 - date of death (retrospective)", "context_label": "Litigation Context", "context_text": "Estate/probate dispute. Two heirs dispute the date-of-death value. Heir A''s appraiser relies on 12-month trailing appreciation to argue Strongly Improving. Heir B''s appraiser relies only on 6-month current data to argue Declining. You must analyze all available data as of August 12, 2022 only, resolve the competing conclusions, and write a complete, USPAP-compliant market condition narrative for the probate court."}, "tables": [{"label": "", "cols": ["Indicator", "Prior Period (Feb-Aug 2022)", "Current Period (Feb-Aug 2022)"], "rows": [["Closed Sales (1-mile radius)", "28", "21"], ["Active Listings", "4", "9"], ["Median Days on Market", "9", "18"], ["Median Sale Price", "$341,000", "$354,500"], ["List-to-Sale Price Ratio", "105.4%", "101.8%"], ["Absorption Rate", "1.4 months", "3.2 months"], ["Pending Sales (as of 8/12/22)", "-", "11"]]}], "external": "Mortgage rates rose from approximately 3.8% in February 2022 to 5.2% by August 12, 2022. The Wade Hampton/Augusta Road corridor is a historically stable in-town Greenville neighborhood with consistent long-term demand from buyers prioritizing school district access and downtown proximity. Prior rate increases dampened demand beginning in May-June 2022. Heir A''s appraiser uses full 12-month trailing data (+12.1% year-over-year) to support Strongly Improving. Heir B''s appraiser uses only 6-month current period data to support Declining.", "factors": [{"id": "abs", "label": "Absorption rate trend"}, {"id": "dom", "label": "Days on market trend"}, {"id": "lts", "label": "List-to-sale price ratio trend"}, {"id": "msp", "label": "Median sale price trend"}, {"id": "inv", "label": "Active listing inventory level"}, {"id": "pend", "label": "Pending sales count"}, {"id": "rate", "label": "Mortgage rate trajectory"}, {"id": "trail", "label": "Heir A''s 12-month trailing appreciation analysis"}, {"id": "heir_b", "label": "Heir B''s current-data-only analysis as controlling"}, {"id": "post", "label": "Post-effective-date data (Fall 2022 price corrections)"}], "net_conclusion": "Transitioning market as of August 12, 2022 - moving from peak seller''s conditions toward balanced. Neither expert''s position is fully defensible. Heir A overstates improvement with trailing data. Heir B overstates decline by ignoring the pending count and still-rising price. Correct characterization: Market-Dependent/transitioning. A modest positive time adjustment may be supportable, but the appraiser must acknowledge the transitioning market in the narrative.", "commentary": "Scenario 10 is the capstone litigation scenario. Students must evaluate two flawed expert positions, reconstruct the correct analysis from raw data, and produce a probate-court-quality narrative. The key skills: (1) identifying methodological flaws in both experts'' data selection; (2) correctly classifying transitioning signals without overcorrecting in either direction; (3) using the pending sales count as a moderating factor; and (4) articulating why post-effective-date data is inadmissible regardless of which party it favors.", "classification_options": ["Improving", "Stable", "Declining", "Market-Dependent"], "min_rationale_chars": 20}'::jsonb,
  '{"factors": {"abs": {"present": true, "classification": "Market-Dependent", "rationale": "Rose from 1.4 to 3.2 months as of August 12 - significant shift from peak seller''s to approaching balanced. Market-Dependent accurately captures this transitional state as of the effective date."}, "dom": {"present": true, "classification": "Declining", "rationale": "Doubled from 9 to 18 days - demand velocity clearly slowing as of the effective date. Heir B is directionally correct on this indicator."}, "lts": {"present": true, "classification": "Declining", "rationale": "105.4 to 101.8% - substantial loss of over-ask premium as of August 12. A meaningful softening signal in the current period data."}, "msp": {"present": true, "classification": "Improving", "rationale": "Still rising +3.9% as of August 12 - a lagging indicator. Neither expert should over-rely on this alone. Prices reflect transactions that closed under prior conditions."}, "inv": {"present": true, "classification": "Declining", "rationale": "More than doubled from 4 to 9 - a leading indicator of demand softening present as of the effective date."}, "pend": {"present": true, "classification": "Stable", "rationale": "11 pending vs. 9 active as of August 12 - demand has not collapsed. This is a critical moderating factor that prevents an overstated Declining conclusion. A leading indicator Heir B''s analysis ignores."}, "rate": {"present": true, "classification": "Declining", "rationale": "Rates rose from 3.8% to 5.2% by August 12, 2022 - a documented, material external factor suppressing buyer activity. Operative and contemporaneous as of the effective date."}, "trail": {"present": false, "rationale": "METHODOLOGICAL DISTRACTOR: 12-month trailing data allows the prior strong period to obscure current softening. This is the same flaw as Expert B in Scenario 7. The trailing figure is not wrong as a data point, but using it as the basis for market condition classification is methodologically flawed."}, "heir_b": {"present": false, "rationale": "METHODOLOGICAL DISTRACTOR: Heir B''s 6-month analysis is directionally more accurate but overstates the decline by ignoring the pending count and the still-rising price indicator. A complete analysis uses all available contemporaneous data, not a selective subset."}, "post": {"present": false, "rationale": "CRITICAL DISTRACTOR: Fall 2022 price correction data - however illustrative - is inadmissible. Regardless of which heir it supports, post-effective-date data cannot be introduced into a date-of-death analysis."}}}'::jsonb
FROM scenarios s
JOIN scenario_categories sc ON sc.id = s.category_id
JOIN module_sections ms ON ms.id = sc.section_id
JOIN section_fields f ON f.section_id = ms.id AND f.field_key = 'market_indicator_analysis'
WHERE sc.code = 'M2-S6-C2'
  AND s.order_index = 10;


