  s.id,
  f.id,
  '',
  '{"subject": {"address_summary": "3817 Paris Mountain Road, Greenville, SC 29609", "subject_summary": "4BR/3BA, 3,480 SF, built 2003, custom home on 2.1-acre lot · Paris Mountain corridor", "school": "Greenville County", "effective_date": "December 15, 2022 - date of death", "context_label": "Estate & Tax Context", "context_text": "Federal estate appraisal for an acreage/custom home property under IRS review. Two data sets are provided: broad market data for Greenville County $400K-$600K residential, and submarket data for acreage/rural-adjacent product in the same price range. You must define the correct market area, identify submarket divergence, and form an independent conclusion."}, "tables": [{"label": "", "cols": ["Indicator", "Broad Market (Prior)", "Broad Market (Current)", "Submarket (Prior)", "Submarket (Current)"], "rows": [["Closed Sales", "98", "72", "11", "7"], ["Active Listings", "41", "58", "4", "8"], ["Median DOM", "22", "41", "31", "58"], ["Median Sale Price", "$488,500", "$471,200", "$512,000", "$491,500"], ["List-to-Sale Ratio", "100.4%", "97.1%", "99.8%", "95.4%"], ["Absorption Rate", "3.8 months", "6.2 months", "4.2 months", "9.1 months"]]}], "external": "Mortgage rates rose to 6.5-7.0% by December 2022, creating significant demand reduction across the price range. Acreage and rural-adjacent properties experienced a disproportionate demand decline as buyers reconsidered longer-commute, larger-lot properties when remote work expectations moderated. Late fall and winter inventory patterns also affect the acreage market more acutely than the suburban market.", "factors": [{"id": "b_abs", "label": "Broad market absorption rate trend"}, {"id": "b_dom", "label": "Broad market days on market trend"}, {"id": "b_msp", "label": "Broad market price trend"}, {"id": "s_abs", "label": "Submarket absorption rate trend"}, {"id": "s_dom", "label": "Submarket days on market trend"}, {"id": "s_msp", "label": "Submarket price trend"}, {"id": "s_lts", "label": "Submarket list-to-sale ratio trend"}, {"id": "rate", "label": "Mortgage rate shock"}, {"id": "rwmod", "label": "Remote work moderation / acreage demand softening"}, {"id": "seas", "label": "Seasonal inventory effect on acreage market"}, {"id": "post", "label": "Post-effective-date data"}, {"id": "broad", "label": "Broad market data as the controlling market area"}], "net_conclusion": "The appropriate market area is the acreage/rural-adjacent submarket. Conditions are declining significantly as of December 15, 2022, materially outpacing the already-declining broad market. A meaningful negative time adjustment is warranted. The remote work moderation factor is a documented, submarket-specific external driver of the divergence.", "commentary": "Scenario 9 combines submarket divergence analysis with the estate hard wall. The methodological distractor is particularly relevant in estate practice, where appraisers sometimes default to metro-wide data when the subject''s competitive market is a narrower submarket. The seasonal factor tests whether students can distinguish a direction-uncertain factor (Market-Dependent) from a clearly negative one. Expert students must identify and articulate all three layers: broad market, submarket divergence, and submarket-specific external factors.", "classification_options": ["Improving", "Stable", "Declining", "Market-Dependent"], "min_rationale_chars": 20}'::jsonb,
  '{"factors": {"b_abs": {"present": true, "classification": "Declining", "rationale": "3.8 to 6.2 months - broad market transitioning to buyer''s territory as of December 15, 2022. Contemporaneous data."}, "b_dom": {"present": true, "classification": "Declining", "rationale": "22 to 41 days - meaningful softening across the broad price range as of the effective date."}, "b_msp": {"present": true, "classification": "Declining", "rationale": "-3.5% actual price decline confirmed in the broad market. A declining signal present in contemporaneous data."}, "s_abs": {"present": true, "classification": "Declining", "rationale": "4.2 to 9.1 months - a dramatic shift into deep buyer''s market territory as of the effective date. Far worse than the broad market and the critical analytical finding."}, "s_dom": {"present": true, "classification": "Declining", "rationale": "31 to 58 days - acreage properties sitting nearly twice as long. The magnitude of this divergence from the broad market is material."}, "s_msp": {"present": true, "classification": "Declining", "rationale": "-4.0% in the submarket - more severe than the broad market decline. Actual price deterioration confirmed in contemporaneous submarket data."}, "s_lts": {"present": true, "classification": "Declining", "rationale": "99.8 to 95.4% - substantial negotiated discounts below asking price specific to the acreage submarket."}, "rate": {"present": true, "classification": "Declining", "rationale": "6.5-7.0% rates as of December 2022 - documented external factor with direct demand impact across the price range."}, "rwmod": {"present": true, "classification": "Declining", "rationale": "Documented submarket-specific factor - buyers reconsidering acreage and commute tradeoffs as remote work moderated. Explains the disproportionate impact on this submarket relative to the broad market."}, "seas": {"present": true, "classification": "Market-Dependent", "rationale": "Late fall and winter seasonality reduces both supply and demand in the acreage segment. The directional impact on price is uncertain - it affects both sides of the supply-demand equation. Market-Dependent is the appropriate classification."}, "post": {"present": false, "rationale": "CRITICAL DISTRACTOR: Post-December 15, 2022 data is inadmissible. The hard wall applies equally to all estate appraisals."}, "broad": {"present": false, "rationale": "METHODOLOGICAL DISTRACTOR: Broad market data understates the severity of decline for acreage product. The subject''s competitive market is the acreage submarket. Using broad data in place of the controlling submarket data is a USPAP market area definition error."}}}'::jsonb
FROM scenarios s
JOIN scenario_categories sc ON sc.id = s.category_id
JOIN module_sections ms ON ms.id = sc.section_id
